<item>
            <title>[LU-2389] move sync out of facet_failover</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2389</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Comments from Andreas,&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;in facet_failover() I still don&apos;t agree with the inclusion of sync before triggering failover (which is apparently from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-924&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite recovery-small, subtest test_105&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-924&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-924&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). That is not how failover works in real life and I think it will hide bugs during testing. Also, a change like that does not belong in a patch which describes only changes for DNE testing. Per inspections in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-924&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite recovery-small, subtest test_105&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-924&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-924&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch (which is where it should be landed), there are AFAIK only a very small number of tests that may be affected by this problem (basically only after a client first mounts or reconnects after eviction and then does nothing in the few seconds before another eviction) so I&apos;d rather add explicit sync to those tests than for every test, or add some mechanism to only force sync updates to last_rcvd for connections during testing.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="16772">LU-2389</key>
            <summary>move sync out of facet_failover</summary>
