                            <comment id="48434" author="adilger" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 15:25:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Was fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1582&quot; title=&quot;replay-ost-single.sh test_8b: client stuck with -115 (-EINPROGRESS)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1582&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1582&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we just need to avoid adding them back.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48433" author="adilger" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 15:24:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, there is some confusion here.  facet_failover() in master does not have any sync calls in it, since commit 5458e96d82a103315095c234c22de0efff7956af landed via &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/3239&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/3239&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1582&quot; title=&quot;replay-ost-single.sh test_8b: client stuck with -115 (-EINPROGRESS)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1582&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1582&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  It is only in your patch that sync calls are being added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
